</ul><h3 id="precon">
    Pre-con sprints</h3>

<p>
    During the weekend before DrupalCon 60 people gathered on Saturday and 100
    on Sunday at <a href="http://www.beursvanberlage.nl/Werk/Berlage-Meet-en-Workspace/#.VEldxovF_jI">The
    Berlage</a>, a fantastic old castle just blocks from the central train
    station. On most days the Berlage serves as co-working space. For 48 hours
    it was home to contributors working together on Drupal core, contrib
    projects, distributions and Drupal.org itself. Our supportive sponsors
    supplied lunch and coffee on both days while contributors worked on a number
    of initiatives: Multilingual, Drupal 8 criticals and beta blocking issues,
    Headless Drupal and REST, porting contrib projects to Drupal 8, Drupal 8
    Frontend United, Search, Drupal.org, Behat (Behavior Driven and
    javascript/frontend testing), Commerce, Panopoly, Rules, Media,
    Documentation, Migration, Performance, Modernizing Testbot, and more.</p>

